anguages offered by the department and will be awarded a minor in Modern Languages  Every cadet who minors in Modern Languages is strongly urged to study in a country where his or her foreign language is the principal tongue  Courses taken elsewhere and requests for alternate configurations of a minor must be approved in advance by the head of the Department of Modern Languages  Institute regulations require a cadet to maintain a C average  2 00 GPA  in all minor courses    Back to Top   Print Degree Planner   Print Friendly Page   All catalogues   2016 Virginia Military Institute  Powered by the Acalog  Academic Catalog Management System   ACMS  Mobile Site 